Professor Yemi Osinbajo – Vice President of Nigeria Remember how a petition was launched in March, prompting the government to implement a sex offenders registry (i.e rape, paedophilia, sexual harassment and assault)? Well, now it’s now live. The Vice-President, Yemi Osinbajo, in collaboration with The National Agency for the Prohibition of Trafficking in Persons (NAPTIP) and other foreign stakeholders, has launched “The Nigeria Sexual Offender Register” today. With this register, victims can now report an incident, go through names of those convicted, speak an adviser and also read & download Violence Against Persons (Prohibition) Act 2015 1 Visit nsod.naptip.gov.ng to learn more. The post Nigeria finally Launches an Official Register of Sex Offenders appeared first on BellaNaija – Showcasing Africa to the world. Read today!. Source: Bella Naija